  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Combine flour, salt, and yeast in a large mixing bowl.",
    "Add softened butter, water, and kefir. Mix until a smooth dough forms.",
    "Knead the dough for 10 minutes until elastic.",
    "Let the dough rest for 1 hour in a warm place.",
    "Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Roll out the dough to 1/4 inch thickness.",
    "Cut out circles of dough using a cookie cutter.",
    "Place a spoonful of apricot jam in the center of each circle.",
    "Top with chopped walnuts and dried apricots.",
    "Fold the dough in half to form a triangle. Press the edges together to seal.",
    "Bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown.",
    "Fry the pirozhki in hot oil until crispy. Drain on paper towels."
  ],
